{"title":"The 9 best leaders’ jerseys in cycling","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/best-leaders-jerseys","date":1737738656000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/best-leaders-jerseys\">The 9 best leaders’ jerseys in cycling</a></p>\n\n<p>Beyond the spectrum of pro team jerseys, cycling’s style gets put to the test in every stage race with a selection of leaders jerseys to help the best riders stand out in the peloton. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Whether it’s transcendent icons like the Tour de France’s yellow jersey or left-field choices of smaller races that need more publicity, there are plenty of leaders’ jerseys in cycling that wouldn’t look out of place on the walls of an art museum.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We’ve ranked our favourites with an honourable mention to a throwback or two that needs to return. Let’s count them down.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>9. Tour de Luxembourg mountains classification</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2173722799-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2173722799-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2173722799-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2173722799-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2173722799-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2173722799-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2173722799-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2173722799-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2173722799.jpg 1024w\" /><figcaption>Tim de Waele/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s not often we see a sleek all-black jersey design. One was previously worn at the Giro d’Italia by the last rider across the line, but this was ended in 1951. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Riders at the men’s Tour de Luxembourg fight for a blue and yellow leader’s jersey while the mountain goats look resplendent in black.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/subscriptions?utm_source=Web&amp;utm_medium=Banner&amp;utm_campaign=Banner+7\" target=\"_blank\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"300\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Subs-flash-160-for-web-7-970x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Subs-flash-160-for-web-7-970x300.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Subs-flash-160-for-web-7-300x93.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Subs-flash-160-for-web-7-768x238.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Subs-flash-160-for-web-7-1536x476.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Subs-flash-160-for-web-7-2048x634.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Subs-flash-160-for-web-7-750x232.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Subs-flash-160-for-web-7-1140x353.jpg 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>8. Baloise Ladies Tour general classification</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2162680908-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2162680908-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2162680908-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2162680908-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2162680908-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2162680908-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2162680908-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2162680908-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2162680908.jpg 1024w\" /><figcaption>Luc Claessen/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Not quite pink, not quite purple. An online colour picker deems this from Baloise Ladies Tour as ‘red-violet’ and it’s simply divine, as seen on Lorena Wiebes at last year’s race.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The minimalist logo of a woman riding her bike is printed across the sleeves is a nice touch. The printing machine must not have been working for SD Worx-Protime though, who had to draw on their logo with sharpie. 11/10 for improvisation.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/2025-worldtour-kit-ranking\">All the 2025 WorldTour kits ranked from worst to first</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/best-pro-jerseys-of-the-2020s-so-far\">The 21 best pro cycling jerseys of the 2020s so far</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/combination-jersey\">Does the combination jersey at the Tour de France have a place in modern cycling?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-d-italia-why-jersey-pink\">The fascinating history of the maglia rosa</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>7. Bretagne Ladies Tour mountains classification</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/bretagne-ladies-tour-2023-photos-etape-3-63-970x647.webp\" alt=\"\" /><figcaption>Bretagne Ladies Tour</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Bretagne Ladies Tour has a whole host of beautiful jerseys to choose from, whether it’s the youth jersey with pink flowers on the sides or a the pink/purple jersey with blue accompaniments. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"885\" height=\"601\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-21-144605.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-21-144605.png 885w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-21-144605-300x204.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-21-144605-768x522.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Screenshot-2025-01-21-144605-750x509.png 750w\" /><figcaption>Bretagne Ladies Tour</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>But the mountains jersey really takes the cake. Won by Lotto’s Thalita de Jong last year, it starts with a blue colour reminiscent of a warm summer’s day and is decorated by pink flowers.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>6. Arctic Race of Norway mountains classification</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"970\" height=\"897\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/FZOQz5JWQAE4spm-970x897.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/FZOQz5JWQAE4spm-970x897.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/FZOQz5JWQAE4spm-300x277.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/FZOQz5JWQAE4spm-768x710.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/FZOQz5JWQAE4spm-750x694.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/FZOQz5JWQAE4spm-1140x1054.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/FZOQz5JWQAE4spm.jpg 1532w\" /><figcaption>Arctic Race of Norway</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>The Arctic Race of Norway’s mountains classification awards a peacock jersey to the best climber. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s marmite and ostentatious but we think it’s spectacular.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>5. Tour Féminin de l’Ardèche stage winner</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Human-Powered-Health-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Human-Powered-Health-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Human-Powered-Health-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Human-Powered-Health-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Human-Powered-Health-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Human-Powered-Health-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Human-Powered-Health-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Human-Powered-Health-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Human-Powered-Health-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Human-Powered-Health-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/Human-Powered-Health.jpg 2000w\" /><figcaption>Human Powered Health</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Riders don’t normally get a jersey for winning a stage, but things are different at the Tour Féminin de l’Ardèche. The six-day race presents the day’s victor with a harlequin-inspired jersey on the podium.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Beat that, EF.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>4. Vuelta a Burgos general classification</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"822\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2165552958-822x970.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2165552958-822x970.jpg 822w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2165552958-254x300.jpg 254w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2165552958-768x906.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2165552958-750x885.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2165552958.jpg 868w\" /><figcaption>Gonzalo Arroyo Moreno/Getty Images</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>No doubt about it, this is one of the best stage race leader jerseys going. The Vuelta a Burgos stretches across four days for the women and five for the men, awarding the top rider with a design akin to an iridescent oil puddle, flecks of pink and blue and purple fighting one another for space.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s almost too similar to the Burgos-BH kit or even to some extent the new SD Worx-Protime jersey, but it’s just so good that who cares?</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>3. Tour de France mountains classification</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"630\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2167290368-630x970.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2167290368-630x970.jpg 630w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2167290368-195x300.jpg 195w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-2167290368.jpg 665w\" /><figcaption>Alex Broadway/Getty Images</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>1975 was an important year in Tour de France history. Not only did it mark the first appearance of the race’s finish on the Champs-Élysées, but also the introduction of the polka dot jersey. Signifying the leader of the mountains classification – which has been in place since 1933 – the red dots on a white background borrows inspiration from Henri Lemoine and later became the wrapping for the chocolate bars of classification sponsor Chocolat Poulain.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now it’s sponsored by E.Leclerc and was most recently seen on the shoulders of Richard Carapaz and Justine Ghekiere.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>2. Tour de France general classification</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-20T142127.259-970x647.png\" alt=\"tour de france femmes 2024\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-20T142127.259-970x646.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-20T142127.259-300x200.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-20T142127.259-768x512.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-20T142127.259-1536x1024.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-20T142127.259-750x500.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-20T142127.259-1140x760.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-20T142127.259-465x310.png 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-20T142127.259-620x413.png 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-20T142127.259-350x233.png 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-20T142127.259.png 1800w\" /><figcaption>A.S.O./Thomas Maheaux</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Is this the most famous jersey in cycling? Ask someone on the street about the yellow jersey and you might just get the corresponding race.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ever since 1919, the leader of the Tour de France has been awarded a yellow jersey. Like the Giro and <em>La Gazzetta dello Sport</em>, its bright colour is derived from the yellow paper used by <em>L’Auto</em>, the newspaper that began organising the race in 1903.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s as iconic as they come but it doesn’t quite reach the top spot…</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>1. Giro d’Italia general classification</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/giro-2024-photography-02-edited-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Giro d'Italia 2024\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/giro-2024-photography-02-edited-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/giro-2024-photography-02-edited-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/giro-2024-photography-02-edited-768x513.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/giro-2024-photography-02-edited-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/giro-2024-photography-02-edited-1140x761.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/giro-2024-photography-02-edited-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/giro-2024-photography-02-edited-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/giro-2024-photography-02-edited-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/giro-2024-photography-02-edited.jpg 1536w\" /><figcaption>Chris Auld</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Giro d’Italia’s <em>maglia rosa</em> is a nod to the pink paper that Italian newspaper (and race creator) <em>La Gazzetta dello Sport</em> is printed on. While the colour is a perfect baby pink that wouldn’t be out of place in the Barbie movie, sometimes it’s the little things that make a good jersey.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Tim de Waele/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/tadej-pogacar\" target=\"_blank\">Tadej Pogačar</a> successfully completed the first half of his historic Giro-Tour double last year, the zip featured the Giro logo. But for 2023, Bruno Armirail wore a jersey decorated with the <em>Trofeo Senza Fine </em>on the zip, which is the trophy awarded to the overall winner.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It blends <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-d-italia-why-jersey-pink\" target=\"_blank\">history</a>, fashion and visibility in the peloton. It doesn’t get better than this.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Honourable mentions</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tour de France: Combination jersey</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"653\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/09/03032726/cor_vos_hinault-970x653.jpg\" alt=\"cyclists in 1980s in yellow, geren and multicoloured jersesy\" /><figcaption>Cor Vos Fotopersburo</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Bring this back immediately. The Tour de France used to run a combination classification from 1968 to 1989 that combined points based on positioning in the main classifications – the rider with the lowest number of points would wear the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/combination-jersey\" target=\"_blank\">combination jersey</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This striking design that combines elements of the other jerseys, like yellow for the <em>maillot jaune</em> and green for the <em>maillot vert</em>, only came into circulation from 1985. It was short-lived sadly as the classification was discontinued after the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/greg-lemond-closest-tour-de-france-ever\" target=\"_blank\">1989 race</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Volta a Comunitat Valenciana: 75th anniversary</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"970\" height=\"485\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/DSC_1542-e1703239493269-2124x1062-1-970x485.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/DSC_1542-e1703239493269-2124x1062-1-970x485.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/DSC_1542-e1703239493269-2124x1062-1-300x150.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/DSC_1542-e1703239493269-2124x1062-1-768x384.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/DSC_1542-e1703239493269-2124x1062-1-1536x768.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/DSC_1542-e1703239493269-2124x1062-1-2048x1024.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/DSC_1542-e1703239493269-2124x1062-1-360x180.jpg 360w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/DSC_1542-e1703239493269-2124x1062-1-750x375.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/DSC_1542-e1703239493269-2124x1062-1-1140x570.jpg 1140w\" /><figcaption>Volta a Comunitat Valenciana</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>2023 marked the 75th anniversary of the Volta a la Comunitat Valenciana and brought special edition jerseys for all the classifications. They’re inspired by the movement of waves from the Mediterranean Sea and bring memories of 90s adverts – specifically for the rainbow art set that packed different colours on the same brush.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Just us?</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/newsletters\" target=\"_blank\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"351\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-970x351.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-970x351.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-300x109.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-768x278.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-1536x556.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-2048x741.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-750x271.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-1140x412.jpg 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/best-leaders-jerseys\">The 9 best leaders’ jerseys in cycling</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Robyn Davidson &#124; Editorial Assistant","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"776281a10669c44157229d7d4d93dad1991bace69a310475025f82c054d7a04b","category":"Cycling"}